.am}}\n\n[[Category:2007 singles]]\n[[Category:Will.i.am songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by will.i.am]]\n[[Category:Songs written by will.i.am]]\n[[Category:2007 songs]]\n[[Category:A&M Records singles]]\n[[Category:Sampling controversies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Got It from My Mama\n| cover      = I Got It From My Mama-single-cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[will.i.am]]\n| album      = [[Songs About Girls]]\n| released   = {{start date|2007|8|2}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   = 2006\u201307;{{unbulleted list|[[Hollywood]], [[California]]|{{small|([[Record Plant|The Record Plant]])<ref name=\"liner\">{{cite AV media notes|others=[[will.i.am]] |title=''Songs About Girls'' |type=CD [[liner notes]] |publisher=[[Interscope Records]] |year=2007}}</ref>}}}}\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 4:03\n| label      = {{hlist|[[will.i.am Music Group|will.i.am]]|[[A&M Records|A&M]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[will.i.am|William Adams]]|Jean-Luc Drion|Dominique R\u00e9giacorte}}\n| producer   = will.i.am\n| prev_title = [[A Dream (Common song)|A Dream]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = [[Baby Love (Nicole Scherzinger song)|Baby Love]]\n| next_year  = 2007\n}}\n\n\"'''I Got It from My Mama'''\" is a [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] song by American [[rapper]] [[will.i.am]]. The uncredited female vocals in the song are from singer [[Kat Graham]]. It was released as the [[lead single]] from will.i.am's third solo album, ''[[Songs About Girls]]''. It's primarily about the inheritance of sexual attractiveness of women through their mother's genetics. The song contains samples of \"Don Quichotte\" by [[Magazine 60]] and \"Take Me to the Mardi Gras\" by [[Bob James (musician)|Bob James]]; Magazine 60 group members Jean-Luc Drion and Dominique R\u00e9giacorte are credited as co-writers on \"I Got It from My Mama\".\n\nThis song was #64 on ''[[MTV Networks Asia|MTV Asia]]''{{'}}s list of Top 100 Hits of 2007.<ref>[[MTV Networks Asia|MTV Asia]]. [http://www.mtvasia.com/Funstuff/Contests/MTVTop100Hits2007/top100.html \"Top 100 Hits List\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071222125424/http://www.mtvasia.com/Funstuff/Contests/MTVTop100Hits2007/top100.html |date=2007-12-22 }}. Retrieved 2007-12-27</ref> [[will.i.am]] later released a remix of \"I Got It from My Mama\", which included a sample from [[Daft Punk]]'s \"[[Around the World (Daft Punk song)|Around the World]]\". Daft Punk denied will.i.am use of the sample. However, a music video was produced with the sample included and featuring [[The Paradiso Girls]]. The opening scene for all of Daft Punk's ''[[Human After All]]'' videos is used for the video.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20071002200025/http://www.thedailyswarm.com/swarm/daft-punk-william-not-my-momma/ Daft Punk to Will.i.am: Not from my Momma] The Daily Swarm. Retrieved on September 27, 2007</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"I Got It from My Mama\" debuted at number #93 on the [[Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. The next week, the song climbed 36 places to number #57. Ultimately, the song peaked at number #31. In Canada, it debuted at #41, the second-highest new entry on the chart that week.\n\n==Music video==\nThe video for \"I Got It from My Mama\" was announced on [[The Black Eyed Peas]]' official website on July 26, 2007, along with a preview of it.<ref>[http://will-i-am.blackeyedpeas.com/ Will-i-am.com - The Official Will.i.am Website<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070922013430/http://will-i-am.blackeyedpeas.com/ |date=2007-09-22 }}</ref> It was fully released on August 2, 2007. The video begins with will.i.am opening a magazine of girls and then the camera descends onto will.i.am sitting on a chair on a Brazilian beach. There are girls walking around and flaunting their bodies to the camera. The video then shows will.i.am singing with the girls while they dance all over him and him sitting on a chair singing.\n\nIn the middle of the video it shows will.i.am on a chair with the girls lying on towels facing him, with an over view on them singing to the camera. At the last verse it shows will.i.am and the same girls at a beach party at night. The video concludes with will.i.am singing at the beach again with the girls and ends with a picture of will.i.am in the magazine saying: \"Brazil: Wish You Were Here!\". After shooting the video, will.i.am shot the video for \"She's a Star\" on a Braziliian beach, at night with special effects reminiscent of [[Duran Duran]]'s \"[[What Happens Tomorrow]]\".\n\n==Usage in media==\n\"I Got It from My Mama\" was featured in several television programs including ''[[CSI Miami]]'' and ''[[Gossip Girl]]''. The hook of the song is sampled in [[Psy (rapper)|PSY]]'s song \"[[Daddy (Psy song)|Daddy]]\".\n\n==Track listing==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* '''Promotional CD single'''\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Radio edit)</small>\u20143:58\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(LP version)</small>\u20144:05\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Instrumental)</small>\u20144:05\n\n* '''UK CD single'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/I-Got-It-My-Mama/dp/B000VDDCQU/ref=sr_1_4?s=music&ie=UTF8&qid=1334421563&sr=1-4 |title=I Got It From My Mama: Amazon.co.uk: Music |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Radio edit)</small>\u20143:43\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>([[Busta Rhymes]] remix)</small>\u20144:12\n\n* '''German CD single'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/I-Got-It-My-Mama/dp/B000VKLVY8/ref=sr_1_1?s=music&ie=UTF8&qid=1334421563&sr=1-1 |title=I Got It From My Mama: Amazon.co.uk: Music |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(LP version)</small>\u20144:05\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Busta Rhymes remix)</small>\u20144:12\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Instrumental)</small>\u20144:05\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Music video)</small>\u20144:00\n\n* '''Digital download'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/i-got-it-from-my-mama-single/id261137169 |title=iTunes - Music - I Got It From My Mama - Single by will.i.am |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2007-08-08 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(LP version)</small>\u20144:05\n\n* '''Digital single'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/i-got-it-from-my-mama-single/id263308844 |title=iTunes - Music - I Got It from My Mama - Single by will.i.am |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2007-09-24 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Busta Rhymes remix)</small>\u20144:12\n\n* '''Digital video single'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/i-got-it-from-my-mama-single/id263950330 |title=iTunes - Music - I Got It From My Mama - Single by will.i.am |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2007-08-07 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Radio edit)</small>\u20143:58\n# \"I Got It from My Mama\" <small>(Music video)</small>\u20144:00\n\n==Charts==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (2007)\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|19|artist=will.i.am|song=I Got It From My Mama|accessdate=October 13, 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|49|artist=will.i.am|song=I Got It From My Mama|accessdate=January 19, 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|46|artist=will.i.am|song=I Got It From My Mama|accessdate=January 19, 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|4|artist=will.i.am|song=I Got It From My Mama|accessdate=January 19, 2014}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Canada ([[Canadian Hot 100]])<ref name=\"billboard1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100#/song/will-i-am/i-got-it-from-my-mama/10610318 |title=The Hot 100 : Page 